ðŸ”¶ 3. Hypothesis Testing
Null & Alternative Hypothesis

Null Hypothesis (Hâ‚€): No effect, no difference

Alternative Hypothesis (Hâ‚): There is an effect/difference

Significance Level (Î±)

Common value: 0.05

Chance of rejecting the null hypothesis when it is actually true.

Type I & Type II Errors
Error	Meaning
Type I Error (False Positive): Rejecting a true Hâ‚€	
Type II Error (False Negative): Not rejecting a false Hâ‚€	
ðŸ”¶ 4. Hypothesis Tests
Z-Test

Used when:

Population variance known OR sample size > 30

Tests mean differences

T-Test

Used when:

Population variance unknown

Sample size < 30

More realistic for real-world data

Chi-Square Test

Used for:

Categorical data

Testing relationship between variables

Goodness of fit

ðŸ”¶ 5. Correlation Analysis

Measures the strength and direction of a relationship between two variables.

Range: âˆ’1 to +1

+1 â†’ strong positive

âˆ’1 â†’ strong negative

0 â†’ no relationship

Pandas:

df.corr()

ðŸ”¶ 6. Linear Regression

Used to predict one value based on another.

Simple Linear Regression

Formula:
y = m x + c

Where:

x = independent variable

y = dependent variable

m = slope

c = intercept

Used for forecasting and trend analysis.

